  {
    "client_msg_id": "bba57693-6de4-4891-b211-18a1db148165",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "Great stuff!\n\n&gt;  Combining a database with its application removes many questions that neither component can answer by itself, such as what indexes are needed, how to shard, the best way to write queries, and how to manage long-running data migrations.\n\nStrongly agree! The holistic approach in Dark is very appealing. Much of the work these days is hand wiring to tie impedance mismatched systems together, with pervasive model duplication. Looks like Dark is going with 'one model' system wide. Reminds me of Jos Jong's Vertically Integrated Architectures book.",
    "user": "U8A5MS6R1",
    "ts": "1551382610.008400",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "user_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
